	(110,1,'2014-07-14 16:55:49','2014-07-14 16:55:49','Richard was most recently an Energy Analyst at Passport Capital, a $3.7 billion global investment management firm located in San Francisco, CA. His primary responsibilities were to analyze and conduct field research on publicly-listed companies in the E&amp;P, oilfield service, and shipping sectors. In addition, Richard was responsible for the firm’s private equity and pre-IPO investments in the energy sector.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Richard was an investment banking Analyst at Deutsche Bank in Houston, Texas within the Natural Resources Group where he advised various domestic and international E&amp;P and oilfield service companies on structured financing solutions for corporate acquisitions, leveraged buy-outs, and contract monetizations (2005-2008).\r\n\r\nRichard earned a B.A. in Mathematical Economic Analysis and Statistics at Rice University (2004).','Richard Shek,  Analyst ','','inherit','open','open','','109-revision-v1','','','2014-07-14 16:55:49','2014-07-14 16:55:49','',109,'http://spidadesign.us/talara/news/109-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
