	(112,1,'2014-07-14 16:56:47','2014-07-14 16:56:47','Binish was most recently Chief Financial Officer of Holden Capital Management, a $225mm group of long / short equity hedge funds. He was responsible for all day-to-day operational aspects of the firm, including fund and management company accounting, daily trade reconciliation, regulatory compliance, investor reporting, and interfacing with prime brokers, auditors, administrators, and lawyers. Serving as the firm’s Compliance Officer, he created company policies relating to employee trading, insider restrictions, regulatory filing, and disaster recovery. Additionally, Binish led the development of several applications designed to evaluate, in real-time,\r\nportfolio exposure and P&amp;L attribution (2007-2010).\r\n\r\nPreviously, Binish was the founder of Xagua Consulting Services, an advisor to family offices and fund of funds. He created a due diligence program to assess operational risk at hedge funds to help investors evaluate potential managers (2003-2007).\r\n\r\nPreviously, Binish was Chief Financial Officer of Anchor Point Asset Management, a New York based global macro hedge fund. He was responsible for setting up the firm pre-launch and managing the operational build-out. Binish designed the firm’s IT and software infrastructure to enable scalability to a multi-billion dollar capacity (2003).\r\n\r\nPreviously, Binish was Chief Financial Officer of Troubh Fund Management, a group of long / short equity hedge funds and managed accounts. Binish managed the firm’s operations and supervised two individuals, helping build the firm from $10mm to $550mm in AUM. He was responsible for all daily operational aspects of the firm, including self administering domestic funds, performing management company accounting, daily trade reconciliation, regulatory compliance, and investor reporting. He managed all relationships with attorneys, administrators, auditors, and prime brokers (1997-2002).\r\n\r\nBinish began his career as an auditor for Rothstein Kass and Grant Thornton. As a Senior Auditor, he spent his entire career auditing numerous multi-billion dollar hedge funds and other investment partnerships (1993-1997).\r\n\r\nBinish earned his B.S. in Accounting from Fairleigh Dickinson University (1994). While at Fairleigh Dickinson, he was Secretary of\r\nthe Accounting Society.','Binish Bulsara','','publish','open','open','','binish-bulsara','','','2014-07-14 16:56:47','2014-07-14 16:56:47','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/talara/?post_type=staff&#038;p=112',0,'staff','',0),
