	(114,1,'2014-07-14 16:57:37','2014-07-14 16:57:37','Joe was most recently a Director at Alternative Access Capital (2010-2013), a firm that provides capital raising and investment advisory services to allocators in alternative investments. While working for Alternative Access Capital, Joe focused on fund marketing, manager due diligence, and hedge fund portfolio customization. Joe was essential in securing investments from some of the world\'s largest banks and in building a custom hedge fund portfolio for a Fortune 100 Company.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Joe was a Senior Associate at New Stream Capital (2006-2010), a $1 billion alternative investment manager with investments in Oil and Gas, Real Estate, Insurance, Consumer Finance, and Private Equity. During his time at New Stream Capital, Joe was responsible for global fund marketing, investor relations, and business development. He often traveled both domestically and internationally to meet with potential investors and represent the firm at industry conferences.\r\n\r\nPrior to New Stream Capital, Joe was an Associate at 1st Alliance Lending (2005-2006), a licensed mortgage lender in Hartford, CT. While at 1st Alliance Lending, Joe worked with individuals on securing mortgage loans and arranging investment property financing.\r\n\r\nJoe earned a B.A. in Government from Connecticut College (2005). He was a 4-year player on the Men\'s Basketball team and was named co-captain his senior season. Recently, Joe has organized charity events for Son\'s of HD, a non-profit charity focused on raising funds and awareness for curing Huntington\'s Disease (\"HD\")','Joseph Tremblay','','publish','open','open','','joseph-tremblay','','','2014-07-14 16:58:01','2014-07-14 16:58:01','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/talara/?post_type=staff&#038;p=114',0,'staff','',0),
