	(101,1,'2014-07-14 16:53:05','2014-07-14 16:53:05','David was most recently a Partner of Perella Weinberg Partners and portfolio manager of a $100mm long / short equities strategy where he was responsible for managing a 5-person investment team (2007-2008). In 2009 and 2010, David originated and conducted diligence on distressed investments in private oil and natural gas properties and public securities as a consultant for Perella and various family offices.\r\n\r\nPreviously, David was a Partner and co-portfolio manager of BrightStream Asset Management, a $150mm long / short hedge fund predominantly focused on the energy, materials, industrial, utility, and consumer sectors. He also had an active role in the firm’s operational build-out and marketing efforts (2005-2007).\r\n\r\nPreviously, David was a Managing Director at North Sound Capital, a $3.0 billion long / short hedge fund founded by a former Managing Director at Tiger Management. He was primarily responsible for $500mm of global investments in natural resource and cyclical sectors. Additionally, David was an advisor for energy sector private investments in an affiliated fund (2002-2005).\r\n\r\nPreviously, David was a Senior Analyst at Pergament Advisors, a New York based multi-family office, and a Senior Analyst at Valenzuela Capital Partners, a New York based institutional money management firm. He was primarily focused on long and short investments in the energy, material, industrial, telecom, and media sectors (1999-2001).\r\n\r\nDavid’s investment career began at Credit Suisse, where he was an Equity Research Associate covering the energy industry. In 1999, he was listed by Institutional Investor Magazine as a best up-and-comer in the natural gas industry (1997-1999).\r\n\r\nDavid earned a B.S. in Commerce from the McIntire School of Commerce at the University of Virginia (1997). While at the University of Virginia, David managed the undergraduate business school’s student fund. He has since been a guest finance lecturer at the McIntire School. He also actively supports the Robin Hood Foundation, a charity targeting poverty in New York City.','David Zusman','','publish','open','open','','david-zusman','','','2014-07-17 16:04:50','2014-07-17 16:04:50','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/talara/?post_type=staff&#038;p=101',0,'staff','',0),
