uest finance lecturer at the McIntire School. He also actively supports the Robin Hood Foundation, a charity targeting poverty in New York City.','David Zusman','','inherit','open','open','','101-revision-v1','','','2014-07-14 16:53:05','2014-07-14 16:53:05','',101,'http://spidadesign.us/talara/news/101-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(103,1,'2014-07-14 16:53:45','2014-07-14 16:53:45','Andrew was most recently a Managing Director at MLH Capital, a $100mm value-oriented hedge fund and family office founded by\r\nthe former Chairman &amp; CEO of Furman Selz. As part of a 3-person investment team, his primary responsibilities were to analyze and conduct field research on companies in the infrastructure, industrial, and consumer sectors. Andrew invested in both the equity and\r\ndebt of publicly traded businesses (2005-2009).\r\n\r\nPreviously, Andrew was an Equity Analyst at Horizon Capital Management, a New York based private investment partnership. He focused on researching micro-cap companies (2003-2005).\r\n\r\nAndrew’s investment career began at Goldman Sachs &amp; Company where he was an Associate in the Private Wealth Management Group. He managed equity and fixed income investments for high net worth families (2001-2003).\r\n\r\nAndrew earned a J.D. from Harvard Law School (2001) and a B.S. in Industrial and Labor Relations from Cornell University (1997). Andrew is a volunteer trial consultant for the Criminal Defense Practice of the Brooklyn Legal Aid Society. Andrew grew up in Virginia, Haiti, and Peru.','Andrew Heyman','','publish','open','open','','andrew-heyman','','','2014-07-14 16:53:45','2014-07-14 16:53:45','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/talara/?post_type=staff&#038;p=103',0,'staff','',0),
