	(107,1,'2014-07-14 16:55:15','2014-07-14 16:55:15','Adam was most recently a Principal at Matrix Capital Management, a $1.0 billion equity long-short fund in the Boston area. His primary responsibilities were to conduct fundamental research and analyze investments in the industrial, consumer, resources, and certain sub-sectors within technology (2009-2011).\r\n\r\nPrior to that, Adam was an Analyst at Perella Weinberg Partners working on David Zusman’s investment team. Adam’s research focused on transportation, logistics, industrials, construction, building products, and business services. Adam joined David prior to the portfolio’s inception and was the third member of the investment team (2007-2009).\r\n\r\nPreviously, Adam was a Senior Associate at Oak Hill Capital Management, where he was a member of the investment team responsible for investing Oak Hill Capital Partners II, LP, a $2.5 billion private equity fund. He was focused on the business services vertical and was involved in all stages of evaluating and consummating transactions in transportation and logistics, equipment rental, airlines, and business process outsourcing. Adam sat as a board observer at RSC Equipment Rental, MeriStar Investment Partners, and Cargo 360 (2004-2007).\r\n\r\nAdam started his career as an investment banking Analyst at Lehman Brothers in New York within the Global M&amp;A and Industrial Groups where he advised industrial corporations and private equity clients on mergers and acquisitions and corporate finance transactions. Adam worked on transactions in the automotive parts industry and waste services industry (2002-2004).\r\n\r\nAdam earned an A.B. in economics, cum laude, from Harvard College (2002).','Adam Taub','','publish','open','open','','adam-taub','','','2014-07-14 16:55:15','2014-07-14 16:55:15','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/talara/?post_type=staff&#038;p=107',0,'staff','',0),
